I use it everyday to manage my zip, tar and gzip archives (I'm a developer)... It's the most quick and efficient I've ever used! Recommended to everyone!

7zip is a good (Free) compression app available. I've been using it for ages but recently i found some issues extracting files that i was successfully able to extract with Winrar. You can not always relay on it and should keep an alternative all the time.

Best compression program ever, I open everythjing with 7-zip. The only archive software I have found that always works flawless. (just right click and extract here, that's the only thing you ever need). Good jub guys.

Great free software for archiving.
Normally MUCH better results than Standard Windows 7  (Zip-compressed folder)
e.g.: Uncompressed: 28 MB
Windows 7 - Standard: 26 MB
7-Zip LMZA2 - self-extracting: 8 MB !!!

I like two panels mode. Shortcuts the same as for Norton Commander. Easy to use and fast.
